            "id": "4553708",
            "title": "Bill Gates withdraws from India AI summit",
            "description": "<html><body><main><div data-page-type=\"basic_article\"><article data-story-id=\"TAOS0TT96OSG00\"><div><div data-ad-size=\"970x250\" data-ad-status=\"rendered\" data-component=\"leaderboard-ad\"><div data-ad-status=\"rendered\" data-testid=\"sparkle-ad\" id=\"leaderboard-decoupled\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"-1\"><div data-google-query-id=\"CJaTsszt5JIDFUemYwYdr10KDQ\" id=\"0f3541991bca6c887812c1a04a55bed6\"><div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/5262/bloomberg/technology/article_0__container__\"></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div><main><div data-page-type=\"basic_article\"><article data-story-id=\"TAOS0TT96OSG00\"><ul>\n<li><span>Microsoft (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MSFT\" title=\"Microsoft Corporation\">MSFT</a></span></span>) co-founder Bill Gates<em> </em>withdrew from India’s AI Impact summit just hours before he was set to deliver the keynote address on Thursday.</span></li>\n<li>\n<span>“After careful consideration, and to ensure the focus remains on the AI Summit’s key priorities, Mr. Gates will not be delivering his keynote address,” the Gates Foundation said in a statement just hours before he was due to speak. </span>No reason was provided for the withdrawal.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-eci=\"true\"> </p>\n<figure class=\"regular-img-figure\" contenteditable=\"false\"><span><img alt=\" \" data-caption=\"\" data-original-src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/attachment/image/8c24e4210d9be14bd6fce0c1d0b1c229.png\" data-rel=\"lightbox\" data-source=\"@BMGFIndia  \" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"691\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1023px) calc(100vw - 180px), 552px\" src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/attachment/image/8c24e4210d9be14bd6fce0c1d0b1c229.png?io=w640\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/attachment/image/8c24e4210d9be14bd6fce0c1d0b1c229.png?io=w480 480w,https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/attachment/image/8c24e4210d9be14bd6fce0c1d0b1c229.png?io=w320 320w,https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/attachment/image/8c24e4210d9be14bd6fce0c1d0b1c229.png?io=w240 240w\" width=\"606\"/></span><figcaption class=\"overlay-title\"><p class=\"item-caption\"><span class=\"item-source\">@BMGFIndia </span></p></figcaption></figure><ul>\n<li>Nvidia (<span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVDA\" title=\"NVIDIA Corporation\">NVDA</a></span>) announced on Saturday that its CEO, Jensen Huang, will not attend the India AI Impact Summit, a major gathering of tech leaders taking place in the country’s capital city of New Delhi.</li>\n<li data-testid=\"paragraph-3\">Prime Minister Narendra Modi is scheduled to address the event on Thursday, alongside French President Emmanuel Macron, Google (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GOOG\" title=\"Alphabet Inc.\">GOOG</a>) CEO Sundar Pichai, OpenAI (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OPENAI\" title=\"OpenAI\">OPENAI</a>) CEO Sam Altman and Anthropic (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ANTHRO\" title=\"Anthropic\">ANTHRO</a>) CEO Dario Amodei.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p></article></div></main></div></article></div></main><div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
